                <p>Pokemon Legends: Z-A is making the grind easier for some key <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/pokemon-legends-za-mega-evolutions-guide/2900-7140/" data-ref-id="2900-7140">Mega Evolution stones</a>, while also getting some fixes in a patch coming in November.</p><p>Fans were irked to learn that the Mega Stones for the Kalos starters (Greninja, Delphox, and Chesnaught) were locked behind ranked matches of the game's <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/pokemon-legends-z-a-is-getting-four-player-battles/1100-6534031/" data-ref-id="1100-6534031">Z-A Battle Club multiplayer mode</a>. While that will still remain the case, the requirements to earn these items will be less demanding come the game's next competitive season.</p>



    
