          <p><em>Now Playing:</em> Pok√©mon Legends Z-A Everything To Know</p>
      </div>
<p>Previously, the expectation was that you could only earn one Mega Stone for one of the three aforementioned Pokemon per season. The first season for Pok√©mon Legends: Z-A featured Greninjite as the reward for reaching rank K (the game starts at rank Z and tops at A).</p><p>But with the second season starting on Wednesday, November 5, at 10 PM PT/1 AM ET, those who missed getting Greninja's Mega Stone can win it by only leveling up once to rank Y, and Delphoxite will be rewarded at the lower rank of S. That's eight ranks lower than the prior season's requirement.</p><p>Should subsequent seasons follow this model, expect Chesnaughtite to be the Season 3 reward. <a href="https://plza-news.pokemon-home.com/en/page/10.html" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">The Pokemon Company also confirmed on its website</a> that the game will adjust points awarded and increase battle rewards after matches.</p><p>It's not a perfect solution, as players will still be required to participate in online matches (which requires a Nintendo Switch Online subscription) to obtain these Mega Stones that could have just been part of the base game.</p><p>Additionally, a <a href="https://plza-news.pokemon-home.com/en/page/9.html" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">patch scheduled for some time in November</a> will address two issues that affect progression in the story. One prevents players from obtaining or catching any new Pokemon if their storage boxes are full before a certain story mission, and another is a glitch that can occur when the game transitions between day and night.</p><p>These changes and fixes to Pokemon Legends: Z-A will come after a largely successful launch for the game, which had a <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/pokemon-legends-z-a-had-the-biggest-physical-game-launch-in-years-in-us/1100-6535737/" data-ref-id="1100-6535737">massive launch in retailers</a>. The monster-catching game is also <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/pokemon-legends-z-a-is-getting-paid-dlc-and-two-shocking-new-mega-evolutions/1100-6534700/" data-ref-id="1100-6534700">getting paid DLC</a> that will include some new Mega Evolutions.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
